Digit separators: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C%2B%2B14#Digit_separators

- VSCode Version: 1.10.2
- OS Version: OSX 10.12.3

Steps to Reproduce:

C++ source code:
t.cpp
```
const int a = 1'000'000;
const int b = 1'000;
const int c = 1;

int main(int argc, char** argv)
{
    return a + b + c;
}
```

This will compile without any error with:
`clang++ -Wall -std=c++14 t.cpp`

but looks like this:
